title: Jessika Power calls Love Island's Vanessa Sierra a 'social climber'
text:
Jessika Power is certainly not afraid to speak her mind.

And the Married At First Sight star, 26, has shared her thoughts on Love Island Australia's Vanessa Sierra, labelling her a 'social climber' after she dated her older brother Rhyce Power.

Speaking to The Kyle and Jackie O Show on Tuesday, Jessika revealed she wants to join Love Island as an intruder so she can confront Vanessa, 24.

'What's your issue with me?' MAFS' Jessika Power (pictured) has labelled her brother's ex-girlfriend Vanessa Sierra a 'social climber' after she appeared as a contestant on Love Island

She said: 'When the [Love Island] promo came out I was just like, "Oh, that's why the social climbing is happening".'

Jessika explained that after Vanessa's split with her brother, she dated her ex-boyfriend Dan Webb, with whom she'd had an affair on MAFS.

When asked about what she thought of Vanessa dating her exes, Jessika said she was no competition.

At war! Speaking to KIIS FM on Tuesday, Jessika revealed she wants to join Love Island as an intruder so she can confront Vanessa (pictured), who also dated her ex-boyfriend Daniel Webb

She also revealed that Vanessa had been 'slagging' her on social media with disparaging comments.

Jessika added that she wants Channel Nine to cast her as a Love Island intruder so she can confront Vanessa directly.

She said: 'I just think, well, I didn’t date you so what's your issue with me? So I'd love to go in there and straighten things up.'

Surprise appearance? Love Island will introduce intruders throughout the series, but it's unclear if producers are considering Jessika

She added: 'I think it would be fun to go in and, you know, have a little bit of a laugh with it and try to find someone potentially [to date].'

Love Island will introduce intruders throughout the series, but it's unclear if producers are considering Jessika.

Love Island Australia continues Tuesday at 8:40pm on Channel Nine
